Text.Value: I'm a friend - I have some food to share.
Snap off your best salute.
Give her your best salute.
You stumble into trouble like a stray pup. My own litter were the same.
I'm sorry.
*The growl only deepens. The hound isn't reassured - or perhaps it is simply taking no chances.*
Stand, soldier! These are the General's private quarters.
*...but it seems the touch is enough, and for a moment the undead beast is just another dog happily wagging its tail.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Re-use animation from player petting Scratch at camp.
EditorData.SFXTags: [EG] Scratching undead dog foley (hands against bone and metal)

Text.Value: But he brought me back. I will not fail him again.
Offer up some food from your pack.
It's a trained army hound - give it your best salute.
Easy - I'm leaving.
*And then it hesitates, gleaming muzzle sampling your scent as if in... recognition?*
Your master's beyond saving. I'm here to end him.
Lower your eyes - you're no threat.
Give the creature a snarl of your own.
Leave.
My scent seemed to trigger a memory in you. What was it?
*Smoky, unblinking eyes fix upon you.*
Pass, then. But I will be watching.
*It turns away and utterly ignores you - as it would any lowly foot soldier.*
Ugh. The General has led many soldiers - and your form is by far the sloppiest.
I cannot tell if your stink is lies or stupidity. It doesn't matter.
I do not know your face, but your scent... Selûnite magic. It used to fill these halls, back when I was flesh.
*Suspicious, the creature leans in for another sniff - and for a moment, its tail wags as if remembering a scent from long ago.*
Your scent is familiar to me, stranger - but I can still smell the lies underneath.
You seemed to know my scent. How?
Would it be all right if I gave you a scratch?
But they are long dead, now. Mind where you stray, lest I send you to join them.
Leave.
Though whichever whelp owns that thing smells... happy. Safe. I have not scented such a thing since I was flesh.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: She hesitates and cocks her head, sniffing the air.
EditorData.NodeContext: She hesitates and cocks her head, sniffing the air.

Text.Value: Stay still and let it sniff you.
*The dog relaxes, as if reassured by your observance of protocol.*
Just be about your task then - whatever it is.
I protect my master. What becomes of his master, I care not.
I... died the same night she did, my master says. Trying to protect her. I do not remember.
Leave.
I let you pass. Do not make me change my mind.
...Wait. Something in your scent is... familiar.
Snarl at the beast's display of weakness.
*Even stripped of flesh, the war-hound is formidable. Spectral eyes meet yours as it growls a challenge.*
I've had no stomach to fill for some time. But you will find my teeth are still sharp, stranger.
*This is not a creature easily cowed, but something in your display gives it pause.*
*The growl withers to a whimper, and the hound turns away, sheepish.*
*Growl.*
My scent seemed to trigger a memory in you. What was it?
Stay still and let her smell you.
To serve Ketheric - as loyally as you do.
Do you take me for a teething pup? Get that out of my face.
Since my master brought me back... this place smells wrong. His family is gone, replaced by bootlickers and beasts.
To make sure your master dies. Screaming, preferably.
You'd be the first of the General's soldiers brave enough to try.
*Growl.*
There will be no screams from you, stranger - not when I take your throat.
No! He may have changed, but he is still my master. I cannot let you pass.
Leave.
*Then the beast shakes its head, a ferocious war-hound once more. Though perhaps not quite as ferocious as before.*
Lower your eyes in respect.
Hm. Hmmm... All right, that's enough.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Re-use animation from player petting Scratch at camp.
EditorData.SFXTags: [EG] Scratching undead dog foley (hands against bone and metal)

Text.Value: *The hound relaxes, clearly accustomed to this show of deference within its master's chamber.*
*Perhaps your form was sloppy. Or perhaps the creature simply wants to taste your blood.*
Show her Scratch's ball.
I'm just exploring the tower. I mean no harm.
I only want to stop the Absolute.
You are neither. So tell me true - what is your purpose here?
...Hmph. Walk carefully, then. Or I will learn exactly what True Soul tastes like.

EditorData.NodeContext: intimidated, but giving a parting shot

Text.Value: *Warily, it watches you approach. There's no flesh or fur to scratch at, only bone and cold metal...*

EditorData.SFXTags: [EG] Scratching undead dog foley (hands against bone and metal)

Text.Value: ...I do not know which army you fight for, but it is not my master's.

EditorData.NodeContext: nonplussed at our terrible salute, attacks

Text.Value: Good. Death itself cannot release you from that duty. Now be about your business, whatever it is.
*Scratch's scent lies heavy on the toy - the scent of play, comfort, safety. For a moment, the skeletal tail twitches.*
No. You are not.
Not your scent - Selûnite magic on your skin. The General once smelled that way, when his daughter still lived.
*The dog's growl only deepens, echoing in the cavity where its stomach used to be.*
Wave Scratch's ball.
You will not walk out again.
Gently reach out to pet the hound.
Yes, soldier?
Down, lapdog. A True Soul walks where they please.
Leave.

Synopsis: The players encounters Ketheric's undead hound in his chambers while sneaking around the tower. She's territorial - but if she smells Isobel's blessing on us she'll recognise Selunite magic. She reveals that she misses the way her master used to be.
